                    <div class="questionHeader">
                        <h3 class="questionTitle">What is the best ski boot size for me?</h3>
                        <span class="toggleIcon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="answer">
                        <p> Finding the right ski boot size is crucial for comfort and performance. We recommend using a size chart that considers foot length in centimeters and your preferred fit. Look for boots that snugly fit without being too tight to ensure you make the most of your skiing experience.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="question">
                    <div class="questionHeader">
                        <h3 class="questionTitle">How do I choose skis suitable for my skill level?</h3>
                        <span class="toggleIcon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="answer">
                        <p>Choosing skis that match your skill level depends on various factors. Beginners might prefer shorter and more manageable skis to aid in the learning process. Advanced skiers may lean towards longer and higher-performance skis. Consult with experts or look for versatile models that align with your skiing style and proficiency level.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="question">
                    <div class="questionHeader">
                        <h3 class="questionTitle">Why is equipment maintenance essential for skiing?</h3>
                        <span class="toggleIcon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="answer">
                        <p>Regular maintenance of ski equipment is vital to ensure optimal performance and extend its lifespan. Regularly waxing and sharpening skis enhance speed and control on the slopes. Additionally, checking bindings and making adjustments ensures safety while skiing. Proper maintenance contributes to a safer and more enjoyable skiing experience.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
