            </h3>
            <p class="historyText">
                In the frost-kissed valleys of the Swiss Alps, Higen emerged as a testament to a dream that began as a spark of passion. Founded in 1995 by a group of skiing enthusiasts led by acclaimed mountaineer, Gregor Heinrich, the company was envisioned to be more than just a business—it was a tribute to the majestic mountains that fueled their ardor. The name 'Higen' derives from the blend of two elements: 'High,' an ode to the lofty peaks that inspire every product, and 'Gen,' symbolizing the genesis of innovative design. From its humble inception in a cozy cabin where ideas were sketched on parchment to the bustling headquarters in Zurich, Higen thrives on a legacy of craftsmanship and innovation. With a focus on quality, each snowboard, ski, and ski pole is meticulously crafted, embodying the thrill of adventure and the precision of Swiss engineering. Higen stands as a testament to the pursuit of excellence, celebrating the beauty of the snow-laden slopes and the exhilaration of gliding down untouched powder with unmatched expertise and passion.
            </p>
